observations.recommendation:
We recommended that management:
Verify the actual ages of the unliquidated fund transfers and request for authority to write-off if the ages of such fund transfers qualify them as dormant unliquidated fund transfers pursuant to COA Circular No. 2016-005 dated December 19, 2016 [Guidelines and Procedures on the Write-off of Dormant Receivable Accounts, Unliquidated Cash Advances, and Fund Transfers of National Government Agencies (NGAs), Local Government Units (LGUs) and Government-Owned and Controlled Corporations (GOCCs)];
Verify the recipient of the July 15, 2014 grant amounting to ₱10,000.00 if it is the Department of Trade and Industry and reclassify it to Due from NGAs if found as such;
Send demand letters to concerned NGOs/POs for liquidation; and
Disqualify the concerned NGOs/POs with unliquidated fund transfers from new fund transfers until their previous fund transfers are liquidated pursuant to COA Circular No. 2007-001 dated October 25, 2007.

Require the City Accounting Office to immediately submit the 1,104 DVs amounting to P15,051,467.41 together with all the supporting documents to the COA for verification and to minimize suspension and/or outright disallowances;
Instruct the City Treasurer’s Office to communicate availability of checks to payees to facilitate the timely payment of government transactions and;
Undertake measures to facilitate the timely and complete submission of the DVs within the first ten days of the ensuing month as required under Section 7.2.1 of the 2009 RRSA.

Consider payment in full of the P27,524,071.34 loan balance with the Municipal Development Fund Office (MDFO) of the Department of Finance, after making a thorough financial analysis of the current cash position of the City Government;

Consider utilizing all available funds before the sourcing – out of resources through loan availment to finance future development projects;

Instruct his financial advisers to prepare a cost-benefit analysis and make a thorough study of the terms and conditions of every loan contract agreement before securing loans in the future to ensure that the resources of the city are not wasted on debt servicing.

We recommended that the City Mayor require the City Engineer to:

Submit the list of all on-going projects/programs/activities and those that are to be implemented this year 2016;

Notify the COA Audit Team that signboards are already posted within ten (10) days after the award of infrastructure projects or before the program/activities started;

Require the Officer-in-Charge of the PPAs to provide signboards in conspicuous places within the premises of the agency and at the PPA’s location; and

4. Consistently, follow the provisions of COA Circular No. 2013-004 in order to attain the State’s policy of transparency and accountability.
